      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Clarendon ¶ 4th May, 1882. ¶ Most highly revered Baron! ¶  ¶ Following your letter of the 26th ult. ¶  I have collected a number of specimens of the leafless  ¶ Drosera ¶ . The flowers appeared before...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">82.05.04</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">From Otto Tepper</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">RB MSS M39, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS removed from a sheet of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Drosera praefolia</seg> (MEL 96850).</p>
               </note>Clarendon</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">4th May, 1882.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Hochverehrtester Hr. Baron!</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In Folge Ihres Briefes vom 26n part. habe ich noch eine Anzahl Spezimen der blattlosen Drosera gesammelt. Die Blumen erschienen, ehe ein Regen den vollkommen ausgedörrten Boden benetzt hatte, und war der letzten ganz hart und trocken um die Knolle herum, die kaum 2 Zoll tief in der Erde steckt.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Jetzt haben die meisten bereits Blätter u. nur wenige blühen noch. Die Petala der normal entwickelten Blüthen u. Pflanzen sind nur etwa halb so breit u. lang, als die von D. Whitakeri, aber gelegentlich finden sich </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">einzelne</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> Pflanzen, die nur eine </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">einzelne</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> Blume aufweisen u. denn ist letzte bedeutend grösser, etwa im Verhältnis wie 3:2. Ob die Pflanze schon im März blühte, kann ich nicht bestimmt sagen, da ich sie zuerst am Charfreitag</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">Karfreitag?</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> beobachtete, es ist aber möglich, da an dem Tage die blühenden Pflanzen schon ziemlich zahlreich sich zeigten.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Einliegend sende ich einige Spezimen in Blättern u. jungen Früchten, sowie mehrere Blumen.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Die Knollen enthalten nicht die Purpurfarbe, wodurch sich die der D. Whitackeri auszeichnen. — Die Blüthen schliessen sich nach Sonnenuntergang.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ueber <name key="Cladium%20trifidum">Cladium trifidum</name> werde ich eine kurze Notiz für die nächste Sitzung der R.S.S.A. einsenden u. versuchen nächstens den einzigen mir bekannten Ort des Vorkommens zu besuchen, um reifen Samen für Sie zu besorgen. Die Kürze der Tage u. Regenwetter beschränken derartige Exkursionen sehr.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hochachtungsvoll verbleibe ich</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Verehrtester Hr. Baron,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ganz der Ihrige</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J G Otto Tepper</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Hrn. Baron F. v. Mueller K.C.G.M. &amp; Ph.D., F.R.S.,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Victoria</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">P.S. Ich werde mich erkundigen mit welchem Schiffe Hrn. Neumann's Eltern von Europa kamen.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Clarendon<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">SA.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">4th May, 1882.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Most highly revered Baron!</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Following your letter of the 26th ult.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to O. Tepper, 26 April 1882 (in this edition as 82-04-26a).</p>
               </note> I have collected a number of specimens of the leafless <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Drosera</seg>. The flowers appeared before any rain wet the completely parched ground, which was quite hard and dry around the tuber, which sits barely 2 inches in the soil.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Now most of them already have leaves and only a few are still in flower. The petals of the normally developed flowers and plants are only about half as broad and long as those of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">D. Whitakeri,</seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">D. whittakeri</seg>?</p>
               </note> but occasionally there are <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">individual</hi>
               </seg> plants with only a <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">single</hi>
               </seg> flower, then the latter is considerably larger, approximately in the proportion of 3:2. I cannot say with any certainty whether the plants already flowered in March, as I noticed them first on Good Friday;,<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">7 April in 1882.</p>
               </note> it is, however, possible, as on that day the plants in flower were already quite numerous.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Enclosed I am sending some specimens in leaf and young fruits, as well as several flowers.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The tubers do not contain the purple dye by which those of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">D. Whitackeri</seg> are distinguished. The flowers close after sunset.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I shall send a short notice about <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Cladium%20trifidum">Cladium trifidum</name>
               </seg> to the next meeting of the R.S.S.A.,<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Royal Society of South Australia. See the report of a paper read to the Society's meeting on 13 June 1882, in the Society's <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Tran</seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">sactions and proceedings</seg>, vol. 5 (1882), p. 113, in which Tepper referred to the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Drosera</seg>, 'seemingly quite new', that 'Baron von Mueller considered a close relation to, but not identical with, <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Drosera squamosa</seg>, a West Australian species'.</p>
               </note> and shall try shortly to visit the only place where I know they occur, to collect ripe seed for you. The short days and the rainy weather greatly limit such excursions.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With greatest respect I remain</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">most revered Baron,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>entirely yours,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J G Otto Tepper.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">P.S. I shall make enquiries as to which ship the parents of Mr Neumann arrived on from Europe.<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to O. Tepper, 25 April 1882.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Cladium%20trifidum">Cladium trifidum</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Drosera%20Whitackeri">Drosera Whitackeri</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Drosera%20Whitakeri">Drosera Whitakeri</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
      </body>
